    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-05-08T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-05-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="108"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d108">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.811/125.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Reinsch</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-05-08">
                            <hi rend="italic">May 8, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>In connection with a note received I saw Foreign Office on Huai River project.
                    Foreign Office favors and will propose to Cabinet assumption by China of the
                    cost of supplementary survey.</p>
                <p>Speedy sending of engineering board much desired though three engineers
                    considered sufficient.</p>
                <p>It has always been kept clear that supervision by American engineer in chief
                    should not in any manner be subject to control of others.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
